Create frontend/src/components/FilterSidebar.jsx

Props: { filters, onFilterChange }
Where filters = { types: [], categories: [], locations: [] }
And onFilterChange(filterType, value, checked) is called when a checkbox changes.

The component renders three filter sections:

Section 1 "Job Type" — checkboxes for: "Full-time", "Part-time", "Internship"
Section 2 "Category" — checkboxes for: "IT & Software", "Marketing", "Design", "Finance", "Engineering", "Sales", "Management", "Human Resources", "Operations"
Section 3 "Location" — checkboxes for: "Bangalore", "Mumbai", "Delhi", "Hyderabad", "Pune", "Chennai", "Gurgaon", "Noida", "Remote"

Each checkbox input is controlled: checked={filters.types.includes(value)} (or .categories or .locations depending on section).
On change, call onFilterChange('types', value, e.target.checked) etc.

Also add a "Clear All Filters" button at top right of the sidebar that calls onFilterChange('clear', null, null).

